============================================================
  ECONOMICS
============================================================

Concept:    Inflation
Category:   Macroeconomics
Definition: General rise in price levels eroding purchasing power
Formula:    Inflation = (CPI_t - CPI_t-1)/CPI_t-1 x 100
Economist:  Irving Fisher
Example:    2022 US inflation hit 9.1%; Fed raised rates to combat it

Concept:    Diminishing Returns
Category:   Microeconomics
Definition: More of one input eventually yields smaller output increases
Formula:    Marginal product falls
Economist:  Turgot/Marshall
Example:    More workers in fixed factory eventually get in each other's way

Concept:    Opportunity Cost
Category:   Microeconomics
Definition: Value of next-best alternative foregone when choosing
Formula:    OC = forgone alternative value
Economist:  Bastiat
Example:    Studying means forgoing wages you could have earned working

============================================================
  QUESTION & ANSWER PAIRS
============================================================

Q1: What is relativity?
A1: Einstein's relativity: Special (1905) — time dilates,
     mass increases at high speeds; E=mc². General (1915) —
     gravity is curved spacetime; explains black holes and
     expanding universe.

Q2: What is entropy?
A2: Entropy measures disorder or randomness in a system.
     The Second Law of Thermodynamics states it always
     increases in isolated systems — the arrow of time.

Q3: What is evolution?
A3: Evolution by natural selection: organisms with
     beneficial traits reproduce more, passing traits to
     offspring. Over generations, populations change. Darwin
     proposed this in 1859.

Q4: What is the speed of light?
A4: The speed of light in a vacuum is 299,792,458 meters
     per second (approximately 300,000 km/s), denoted as c.

Q5: What is natural selection?
A5: Natural selection: individuals with traits better
     suited to their environment survive and reproduce more.
     Over many generations, these traits become more common
     in the population.

